# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Cursor Project Rules  (machine-friendly)
# Every directive uses the form  “ALWAYS …”  for easy parsing.
# Blocks are separated by   ## SECTION   lines.
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

## 📢 MIRROR NOTICE (DO NOT EDIT ONE WITHOUT THE OTHER)
# This `.quarkrules` file is programmatically duplicated from `.cursorrules` to
# ensure that both the Cursor agent and internal Quark runtime enforce the same
# rule-set. Any update to *either* file MUST immediately propagate to the other
# to avoid drift.

ALWAYS forbid any automated or autonomous edit to `.quarkrules` or `.cursorrules`; the system may only SUGGEST changes which must be explicitly approved and manually applied by the user.
